# HR Performance Analysis

A Python-based HR analytics project explore employee performance, detect outliers, and find potential improvement areas.

## ðŸ“Œ Features
- Statistical Summaries: Mean, median, distribution analysis
- Visual Insights:
  - Distribution of performance scores
  - Distribution of hours worked
  - Performance by department
  - Correlation between engagement and performance
- Recommendations: Actionable suggestions based on analysis

## ðŸ—‚ Dataset
The dataset contains employee performance metrics, engagement survey scores, and work-related data.

ðŸ“Š Key Insights
The majority of employees fall into the Fully Meets performance category.

High engagement scores are linked to better performance.

More special projects often correlate with higher performance.

Some departments show notable variations.

ðŸ“Œ Recommendations
Strengthen employee engagement programs.

Investigate cases of high absenteeism or frequent lateness.

Encourage participation in special projects.
